OL,3,CUp to 4,500 people to have assisted
OL,4,Cdeath each year if bill passes
OL,6,FAn impact assessment of the assisted
OL,7,Fdying bill suggests that up to 4,559
OL,8,Fpeople a year would be helped to die
OL,9,Feach year if the legislation passes.
OL,11,FThe research was commissioned by the
OL,12,FHealth Secretary to help inform MPs as
OL,13,Fthey prepare to vote again on the bill
OL,14,Fin two weeks time.
OL,16,FIt concludes that in the first year
OL,17,Fafter legalisation of assisted dying,
OL,18,Fbetween 164 and 787 people would go
OL,19,Fthrough with an assisted death.
