OL,3,CUp to 4,500 people to have assisted
OL,4,Cdeath each year if bill passes
OL,6,FBut that number would rise to between
OL,7,F1,042 and 4,559 ten years later.
OL,9,FThe impact assessment also tries to
OL,10,Festimate the costs of the bill, such
OL,11,Fas the money required to train NHS
OL,12,Fstaff, carry out patient assessments
OL,13,Fand administer drugs.
OL,15,FAll of the costs are estimated to be
OL,16,Fin the low millions of pounds, with
OL,17,Fthe impact assessment concluding that
OL,18,Fthere would also be some small savings
OL,19,Fof up to #60m to the NHS owing to the
OL,20,Ffact that some patients would cut
OL,21,Fshort their care.
