OL,3,CUp to 4,500 people to have assisted
OL,4,Cdeath each year if bill passes
OL,6,FKim Leadbeater, who drafted the
OL,7,Fassisted dying bill, said "I am sure
OL,8,FMPs and others will read these
OL,9,Fdocuments with care, but I am firmly
OL,10,Fof the view that the overall impact of
OL,11,Fthis long overdue reform will be to
OL,12,Fmake end of life care in England and
OL,13,FWales more compassionate and
OL,14,Fsignificantly safer. We cannot afford
OL,15,Fto ignore the injustice and unfairness
OL,16,Fin the current legal framework and I'm
OL,17,Fgrateful to all those in government
OL,18,Fwho have analysed with such care the
OL,19,Fimpact that this legislation, if
OL,20,Fpassed, will have."
