OL,6,FMPs are due to vote on the bill as it
OL,7,Fhas its third reading on May 16th,
OL,8,Fafter passing it by a majority of 55
OL,9,Fat second reading last November.
OL,11,FSources suggest that few MPs have so
OL,12,Ffar changed their mind about the bill,
OL,13,Fthough some are assumed to be waiting
OL,14,Ffor a debate in the Commons before
OL,15,Fdeciding.
